1
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:23,840
♪The world decays, in gloom I stray♪

2
00:00:23,840 --> 00:00:26,900
♪Right and wrong, in frost engraved♪

3
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:32,750
♪On dreams of love, blades clash and sway♪

4
00:00:36,590 --> 00:00:39,240
♪Alone I ride, blood still unswayed♪

5
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:42,370
♪Through heaven's mirth and earth's despair♪

6
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:48,370
♪Toasting the moon, I drink the chill air♪

7
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:52,800
♪Though hearts like battlefields may be♪

8
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:55,300
♪Let fate write its uncertainty♪

9
00:00:55,470 --> 00:00:58,480
♪From this life to the great unknown♪

10
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:05,150
♪Who'll stand with me, on thrones unknown?♪

11
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:10,400
♪I'll wander through this life to guard you♪

12
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:13,660
♪Through mortal realms, serene I roam♪

13
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:17,520
♪With you, the world becomes my home♪

14
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:21,400
♪Unbroken, bold, as I have sworn♪

15
00:01:21,580 --> 00:01:25,970
♪I'll roam this life, and feel no torn♪

16
00:01:26,170 --> 00:01:29,320
♪Our souls embraced, no regret born♪

17
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:33,100
♪By twilight's lamp, though night be worn♪

18
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,750
♪Through deepest dark, I'll find the morn♪

19
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:40,990
=Fight For Love=

20
00:01:41,020 --> 00:01:43,940
=Episode 4=

21
00:02:00,350 --> 00:02:02,200
Madam. Don't, Madam.

22
00:02:02,430 --> 00:02:03,710
Don't do this, Madam.

23
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:04,960
Madam!

24
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:08,790
Madam.

25
00:02:08,790 --> 00:02:09,630
- Chun.
- Chun.

26
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,240
- Chun.
- Chun.

27
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,680
- Chun.
- Chun.

28
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:13,680
Chun, are you all right?

29
00:02:13,950 --> 00:02:14,790
- No.
- Chun.

30
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,200
Let me go.

31
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,040
Chun.

32
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:18,640
How could you

33
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,920
do something so foolish?

34
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,840
On my wedding day, I sprained my ankle.

35
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:24,190
He noticed that

36
00:02:24,190 --> 00:02:25,630
and carried me all the way back.

37
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,120
He even wiped my foot
with medicinal liquor.

38
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:30,800
If I hadn't experienced love,

39
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:32,870
I'd surrender to fate.

40
00:02:32,870 --> 00:02:33,750
But I once had

41
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:34,710
such a wonderful man.

42
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:37,120
I can't spend the rest of my life alone.

43
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,520
Let me go.

44
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,910
Chun. Chun.

45
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:41,590
Chun!

46
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,800
If your death could restart everything,

47
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:45,030
we would not stop you.

48
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:46,960
But what you're doing

49
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,400
will only bring us trouble.

50
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:50,590
It won't help at all.

51
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,470
No matter who dies,

52
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:56,680
life must move on.

53
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,270
That's not true.

54
00:02:58,590 --> 00:02:59,430
That's not.

55
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:00,590
Let me go.

56
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:01,470
Dying is easy.

57
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:04,120
But what about Lingchun?

58
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,360
Lingchun.

59
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:10,990
Lingchun, my son.

60
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:13,190
You and Shu loved each other.

61
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,630
Lingchun has lived happily
since he was born.

62
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:19,120
Suddenly, he lost his father.

63
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:21,520
How could you let him
lose his mother too?

64
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,680
Chun.

65
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,150
All men in our family

66
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,000
are unyielding.

67
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:30,800
Your husband not only defended

68
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,310
our nation and its people.

69
00:03:33,240 --> 00:03:36,360
He also wanted you to be carefree.

70
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,640
Chun,

71
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:41,800
you are his wife

72
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,560
and madam of the second branch.

73
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:46,870
My eldest son never married.

74
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,360
So, you're just like

75
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,080
my eldest daughter-in-law.

76
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,680
You've been taking care of this family

77
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,310
and haven't put a foot wrong.

78
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:58,160
(Wei)
Now,

79
00:03:58,190 --> 00:04:00,120
I'm entrusting you
with the Commanding Jade Seal

80
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,680
of this family.

81
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,310
Hope you will not

82
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,080
(Wei)
let me down.

83
00:04:07,590 --> 00:04:08,430
Chun.

84
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,400
- Madam.
- Chun.

85
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,640
Mother,

86
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:26,750
I won't do such a foolish thing again.

87
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:28,630
I promise you.

88
00:04:29,590 --> 00:04:30,590
Unless I'm dead,

89
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:33,390
I will always protect this family.

90
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:38,920
Don't cry, Chun.

91
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,120
- Mother.
- Don't.

92
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:47,430
Mother.

93
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:48,590
Chun.

94
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,200
(Wei Yun,)

95
00:04:53,510 --> 00:04:54,800
(you didn't protect your family.)

96
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,240
(You're in no position to comfort them.)

97
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:36,590
Chu Yu.

98
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:38,590
What on earth

99
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:40,110
do you want from us?

100
00:05:46,310 --> 00:05:47,150
What do you mean?

101
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:48,680
My big brother is dead.

102
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,040
But you're determined to be his widow.

103
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:53,000
What on earth

104
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,160
are you up to?

105
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,510
What if I simply like Wei Jun?

106
00:05:58,720 --> 00:05:59,720
Others may

107
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,630
buy that lie.

108
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:01,560
But you won't fool me.

109
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,150
You made a scene
at the Spring Breeze House

110
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,590
and you came here today.

111
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:08,040
You've been plotting this all along.

112
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,000
Is it for my big brother

113
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:14,000
or actually for this family?

114
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:17,350
Wei Yun,

115
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,270
instead of suspecting my purpose,

116
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,870
why don't you think

117
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,750
about how you can get justice

118
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,630
for your lost family and dead soldiers?

119
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,080
Yun.

120
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,520
Back in there,

121
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,620
you saved Chun in time.

122
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:51,630
I had my reservations about you.

123
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,240
- Now...
- Mother.

124
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,680
Don't let her fool you.

125
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:00,000
Stop being so rude to her.

126
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,760
I'm going to the mourning hall.

127
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:37,120
Yun is

128
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,040
in great distress.

129
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,680
If he comes off as offensive,

130
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,120
please don't mind.

131
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,910
I won't.

132
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,000
It's not easy for you to trust me.

133
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,350
And anyway,

134
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:51,680
Wei Yun had a narrow escape

135
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,680
from the battlefield.

136
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,920
I have something to say as well.

137
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:04,000
You're a different daughter-in-law.

138
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:05,720
My eldest son

139
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,430
didn't marry you

140
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,800
with a formal wedding.

141
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,750
After the funeral,

142
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:11,720
you can think it through.

143
00:08:12,430 --> 00:08:14,000
You're free to go home anytime.

144
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:16,950
Do not waste

145
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,360
your youth here.

146
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:24,270
All right.

147
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,360
I'll think it through

148
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:27,950
and let you know.

149
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,600
Before, Brother and I

150
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:47,600
tried really hard,

151
00:08:47,950 --> 00:08:49,480
only to find out about a mountain.

152
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,630
You think you can get more information

153
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,000
by simply rummaging around?

154
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,480
I was just trying to see

155
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,720
what I could do to help.

156
00:08:57,910 --> 00:08:59,360
You must not touch

157
00:08:59,510 --> 00:09:00,350
Mr. Wei Jun's stuff.

158
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,840
Since Father died,

159
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,120
I've locked up

160
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:15,960
his study.

161
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,150
Everything in there

162
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:19,440
is kept the way it was.

163
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,840
Every time I see it,

164
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,750
I feel as if he were still around me.

165
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:40,670
Mr. Wei Jun was upright and honest.

166
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,510
Pretend I'm doing the same

167
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,870
for his own brother.

168
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:49,560
What's wrong?

169
00:09:50,630 --> 00:09:51,470
Let me see.

170
00:09:54,910 --> 00:09:56,150
How did it end up like this?

171
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,800
You leave it alone.

172
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:07,630
Does it hurt?

173
00:10:11,390 --> 00:10:12,870
It's the first day you've been here

174
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,480
and you're already hurt.

175
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,030
What's going to happen in the future?

176
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:21,800
My Lady,

177
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,290
what are your plans?

178
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:27,040
We'll help them through this crisis.

179
00:10:29,180 --> 00:10:30,900
They're in such big trouble.

180
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:32,300
Maybe it's related

181
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:34,340
to the leak of the octagonal crossbow.

182
00:10:35,540 --> 00:10:37,020
I'm at the center of the vortex

183
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:39,300
and I have to be involved.

184
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,140
Otherwise, I will be consumed by it.

185
00:10:42,740 --> 00:10:44,300
But I see General Wei Yun

186
00:10:44,540 --> 00:10:46,300
press you really hard.

187
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:48,420
I'm afraid

188
00:10:48,660 --> 00:10:49,940
you will have a really hard time

189
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:51,340
in this mansion.

190
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:54,980
I'm worried that...

191
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:56,260
Don't worry.

192
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,580
Mr. Wei Jun just died in battle.

193
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:01,060
I suddenly

194
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:02,820
became his widow.

195
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,260
If I were Wei Yun,

196
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:05,340
I'd be suspicious too.

197
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,700
Once I find out the truth, I will leave.

198
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:11,340
I don't want to be a burden.

199
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:14,220
As for Wei Yun...

200
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:17,820
We'll cross that bridge

201
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:18,900
when we come to it.

202
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:25,300
(True Might)

203
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:31,020
Kneel.

204
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:06,900
Read the funeral oration

205
00:12:07,220 --> 00:12:09,900
to tell their stories.

206
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:25,380
The 27th day of the 7th month

207
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:27,660
marked the border crisis.

208
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:31,300
My father, brothers, and I rushed there.

209
00:12:32,380 --> 00:12:34,580
We fought for seven days and nights

210
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:36,860
before repelling the enemy.

211
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:39,660
That night, we drank.

212
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,620
My brothers and I

213
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:44,100
got drunk on the city tower.

214
00:12:45,780 --> 00:12:46,660
I was too young

215
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,180
to know the life meaning.

216
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:50,660
So, I asked my brothers

217
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:53,060
what they would wish for.

218
00:12:54,460 --> 00:12:55,300
My big brother said

219
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:57,580
he wished for world peace

220
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,980
and justice everywhere.

221
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,420
My other brothers hailed.

222
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:06,900
I asked again,

223
00:13:08,740 --> 00:13:09,700
"In case of world peace,

224
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:12,980
what will you want to do?"

225
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,940
(Wei's Ancestral Hall)

226
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:16,380
My brother smiled and replied,

227
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:20,060
"Watch the willows in spring.

228
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:23,100
Enjoy the snow in winter.

229
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:26,300
Drink with friends

230
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:28,940
and get drunk in the restaurant.

231
00:13:29,940 --> 00:13:31,780
It's dangerous on the battlefield.

232
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:35,060
Yet it's romantic in Huajing City.

233
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:38,980
We're just ordinary guys.

234
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,180
Whatever happens,

235
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,420
we'll go back to loving families.

236
00:13:49,820 --> 00:13:50,660
That's enough."

237
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:57,820
First come, first draw.

238
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:59,100
- Yun.
- Yun.

239
00:13:59,100 --> 00:13:59,940
Don't cheat.

240
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:00,860
Father.

241
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:03,020
When will Yun

242
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,820
truly grow up?

243
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:06,660
Father, if he can always

244
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,100
remain so carefree,

245
00:14:08,740 --> 00:14:09,580
isn't that great?

246
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:31,900
(Wei)

247
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,500
Raise the coffins!

248
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,690
Isn't he the Minister
of the Court of Judicial Review?

249
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:09,660
What's he doing here?

250
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,460
I'm Minister Cao Yan of the Court.

251
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:18,180
I was sent to get sinful Wei Yun.

252
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:26,220
Mr. Cao,

253
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:29,380
what crime did I commit?

254
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:32,860
Your family overreached,

255
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,700
causing the death of 70,000 soldiers

256
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:35,900
in Baidi Valley.

257
00:16:36,180 --> 00:16:37,020
Even in death,

258
00:16:37,420 --> 00:16:38,540
they are held responsible.

259
00:16:49,140 --> 00:16:50,180
Oh, I see.

260
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:51,420
All those soldiers

261
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,860
lost their lives in vain

262
00:16:52,860 --> 00:16:54,060
just because of your family!

263
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:55,940
Thousands of our soldiers

264
00:16:56,340 --> 00:16:57,460
spilled their blood

265
00:16:57,460 --> 00:16:58,460
and gave their lives

266
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,140
to contribute for a century

267
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:01,460
to your family's glory.

268
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:03,900
How could you still be greedy?

269
00:17:04,580 --> 00:17:05,940
The Weis are murderers.

270
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,460
Since Wei Yun is still alive,

271
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:08,620
hold him accountable.

272
00:17:08,980 --> 00:17:11,100
- Hold him accountable!
- Hold him accountable!

273
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:14,060
We demand justice from the court!

274
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:23,940
We demand justice! We demand justice!

275
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:26,540
General Wei Yun,

276
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:28,100
did you hear?

277
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,740
This is what our people want.

278
00:17:31,940 --> 00:17:32,940
I advise you

279
00:17:32,940 --> 00:17:34,500
not to resist arrest.

280
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:35,860
Otherwise,

281
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:37,460
I'll have to be rude.

282
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:53,300
Yun.

283
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:09,140
It's him.

284
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:10,620
- It's him.
- It's him.

285
00:18:10,620 --> 00:18:12,340
What are you doing? Stop it.

286
00:18:12,340 --> 00:18:13,660
- Stop.
- Lan, be careful.

287
00:18:15,020 --> 00:18:15,860
Stop it.

288
00:18:15,860 --> 00:18:16,700
